  "texts": [
    "Figure 3 [A] shows an expanded table in Scholar QA where related papers from a section are compared across a set of common aspects ([B]).",
    "Scholar QA is open-sourced as an extensible Python package (ai2-scholar-qa) and a Typescript and React-based interactive web application.",
    "The LLM functionality of Scholar QA is implemented with litellm, which supports swapping a variety of models using your own keys.",
    "Thus, the community can build upon Scholar QA and easily visualize the results (examples in Appendix A).",
    "Below we describe the user experience of the demo."
  ]
}